title: Expanding Exports is Focus of Greater Baltimore Committee's Economic Outlook Conference
text:
Greater Baltimore Committee
BALTIMORE, Oct. 15, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ -- Greater Baltimore Committee to release Baltimore metro export plan at Economic Outlook Conference.
WHAT:
Annual GBC Economic Outlook Conference
WHEN:
Monday, October 19, 2015
8 a.m. program start
WHERE:
Hyatt Regency Baltimore, 300 Light St., Baltimore, MD 21202
WHO:
Guest Speaker : Marek Gootman, Fellow and Director, Strategic Partnerships and Global Initiatives, Brookings Institution.
Forecast for the 2016 Economy Presenter: Richard E. Cripps , Chief Investment Officer, Stifel.
DETAILS:
The GBC Economic Outlook Conference will focus on "Expanding Into Global Markets: Exporting your Goods and Services to Grow your Business."
Experts will discuss how the Greater Baltimore region can expand and improve export activities to stay competitive in today's global economy as part of its work on the Global Cities Initiative, a joint project of the Brookings Institution and JPMorgan Chase.
At the event a report with an assessment and study findings of the Baltimore metro region's current exports and the potential for growth will be released and discussed.
The Baltimore region, led by the GBC and partner organizations, was accepted in early 2015 to participate in the Global Cities Initiative.
Members of the media planning to attend and cover the event should contact one of the GBC media representatives listed for press clearance.
